Add Stage 2 Post-Load Fix: patch PROCESSOR HDF5 attribute (hyp3 -> isce)

MintPy's hybrid ISCE2/Dolphin pipeline needs two different PROCESSOR
labels at two different moments: 'hyp3' during load_data (so the GDAL
reader decompresses Dolphin's LZW GeoTIFFs) and 'isce' afterwards (so
check_loaded_dataset picks the radar-geometry lookup path via
/latitude + /longitude). Keeping 'hyp3' after load_data raises:

    AttributeError: Unknown InSAR processor: hyp3 to locate look up table!

This change adds an explicit second stage to the workflow that patches
the HDF5 PROCESSOR attribute on ifgramStack.h5 and geometryRadar.h5
once load_data has succeeded.

- New src/dolphin2mintpy/postprocess.py module with
  fix_processor_attribute() and verify_inputs_dir(); refuses to patch
  when geometryRadar.h5 lacks /latitude or /longitude datasets.
- GUI becomes a two-tab notebook:
    1. Prepare (pre load_data) - the existing form, now labelled and
       followed by a "Next step" hint pointing at load_data.
    2. Post-Load Fix - inputs/ picker, old/new processor dropdowns,
       target file list, prominent warning banner, Verify + Apply fix
       buttons with their own log pane.
- CLI subcommand: dolphin2mintpy fix-processor --inputs-dir ...
  with --verify-only, --dry-run, --from, --to, --targets,
  --skip-lookup-check.
- h5py added to runtime dependencies.
- Public API now exposes fix_processor_attribute, verify_inputs_dir,
  PostProcessError.
- 8 new pytest cases cover verify / patch / dry-run / idempotency /
  missing lookup / skip-check / missing dir.
- README rewritten around the two-stage workflow:
  * New "Two-stage workflow at a glance" table.
  * Updated UI table describing both tabs.
  * CLI example now includes the full ISCE2->Dolphin->load_data->
    fix-processor->SBAS sequence.
  * Classic MintPy errors table extended from 4 to 5 rows, with the
    new AttributeError explicitly mapped to Tab 2 / fix-processor.
- Removed the standalone fix_processor_attr.py helper script; its
  logic now lives in the package.
